,Recommended,260160,11041930,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,Dr̀acu͜laf̸e͡t͏us̀,"Let me start by saying that you need to play this if you have the slightest interest in platform games. The further you get into the game the more inspirations you can see the developers adapted and put their own spin on it. If you like Psychonauts, Mario Sunshine, Banjo Kazooie, Jak and Daxter then this game is a must play. Everything feels nostalgic and really great.The story itself is surprisingly good and it was enough to keep me interested throughout. There wasn't a point when the story got in the way or pushed it in your face, it was subtle and benefited strongly from that.The visuals are super colourful and the art style is impressive also. The character and world designs never got boring. The game also supports colourblind mode in case you need that.The only negative I can think of is the combat, the game kinda forces you to use certain moves to kill certain enemies. Some of them will be shielded, some will just kill you in 1 hit. While it adds a lot of variety in combat it sort of gets repetitive. It has a combo system that's hardly implemented which is a shame. And seeing as fighting is what you do 80% of the time it kinda slows the pace down.You should highly consider playing this tho. It took me around 8 hours to finish on and off. Aside from the story there are collectibles to find also, you can go back to areas at anytime in case you missed them giving it more replay value."
76561198020506980,Recommended,260160,26486356,"Posted: 8 November, 2016",all,Oybluz,"TL;DR : Description gives wrong expectations, but the game is still fun. This is more an adventure game than a platformer.Many people complain that this is not a difficult/challenging platformer. But it's not meant to be. It's a kid-friendly, easy platformer. So of course most of the platforming and combat is easy, and a lot of things are automated. The problem comes from the ""inspired by"" part of the description. This proves once again it's rarely a good idea to say your game is inspired by this or that because people will expect a very similar game and be disappointed.The game may be wrongly advertised, but that doesn't mean the game is bad. You just have to expect a fun and colorful, kid-friendly (both in terms of content and difficulty) adventure game with platforming elements. Not an actual platformer like the two games this one is said to be inspired by."
,Recommended,260160,33051067,Posted: 30 June,all,huskobon,"A cool concept with a lot of loveThe Last Thinker is a fun action/adventure game that holds it's own with an interesting set of characters and designs and borrows from classics we know, such as Wind Waker, and Jak & Dexter.  Game is about Koru, a Monkey who was one day just trying to win a race, and landed up down the road causing the apocalypse of colors.  You are set on a journey to restore the colors, and restore peace to the land, as you battle white and grey monsters with the power of color.  It's a cool concept, and a lot of fun!   At times, the camera can be a little clunky, causing loading issues, but the game runs really good for the most part. Sometimes the story can feel a little bit like cardboard, but it's not a big deal, because where it lacks, it still comes back into.  There's not much voice acting, besides the intro. The characters make funny sounds to talk in their dialogue bubbles.    I got this on sale, and it's well worth it. It's well produced, and fun to play, and worth your time if you love a good action/adventure game.7/10"
