76561197960318168,Recommended,260160,30407545,Posted: 9 March,all,Online-Loser,"This game needs more attention, therefore this review.The Last Tinker tells a story of a town where people of different colors live seperated from each other, because of distrust and prejudices. It is the players task to overcome the differences and bring the city back together.The game is very atmospheric, colorful, funny and is adressed to younger players, although adults can have fun with it too. Besides the vivid colors, there is a great soundtrack which reminds me a bit of Bastion.The greatest weakpoint is the gameplay. I would not call this game a ""platformer"" because the jumping is done automatically. Combat is okay. Your punches can have different effects on the enemy, which opens up some variety.Overall this very kid-friendly game tells a nice story about problems, that we all encounter on a daily basis. If you can bear the lack of gameplay you will enjoy the game."
76561197983186143,Recommended,260160,30800917,Posted: 28 March,all,Storywriter,"IN SHORT: This is a wonderful game if you like colorful worlds, a nice (and surprisingly touching) story and easy-going gameplay. It is a smooth ride with the occasional challenge here and there. Clearly the makers put in a ton of love and it shows this everywhere.Full review below.Pro+ Vibrant and colorful world, bitesize levels which fit together coherently.+ An easy and relaxing ride.+ Nice story with some clever morals (great for kids as well!)+ If you look carefully, eastereggs + collectables.+ Good mechanics around fighting and solving puzzles.+ Amazing soundtrack!Con- Not for people who look for the ultimate challenge.- Not exactly ""platforming"", this is automated platforming.Playing The Last Tinker was a great experience. It reminds a lot of the platform games of old, like from the N64 period. But let's get one thing out of the way straight away: this game took a simpler approach to platforming. In terms of gameplay this means 2 things.1: It removes all challenge for the real platforming fans out there.2: this means the game needs to deliver in different areas to make it up.In my humble opinion I would say it does the latter nicely. The charm of this game is unmistakeable. The game is set in one big colorful world split up in bitesize levels and is really fun to explore. At some point in the story the world is attacked by the ""bleakness"" which is draining all colors. This means you usually get to see 2 versions of a level. One filled with bleakness and one where it has been cleansed. It is rewarding to return the world to its original looks.The game has a great story which dares to touch our world's problems (racism for one). Also I could not help but start caring for the inhabitants. Even though communication is done via simple text clouds, it manages to convey the message how the creatures feel about all the happenings. Some are scared, others angry, others sad and hopeless. Not only does this fit with their colors, but it also makes sense and is relatable.Apart from the ""platforming"" the game offers just enough combat varience and puzzles to be entertaining. Think along the lines of opening doors by pressing buttons, lowering bridges, guiding helpful creatures with their own abilities (like exploding), finding keys or items, etc. Nothing new, but entertaining anyway.I also like how the creators experiment with different genre types (even trying ""noir"" at some point), and how they created some mini-games which actually complement the story.To top it all off, this game has an amazing soundtrack. Each part of the world is complemented by its own instrumental style. I especially liked the music from the noir level and the blue world in general.I would say this game is just long enough for what it tries to accomplish. I have had a great time and even felt some genuine emotion here and there. Technically this game also performs great. I had no bugs or issues at all, had steady FPS (though to be fair my pc is quite strong), and found the controller support excellent.As I wrote above, this game clearly shows the creators invested a lot of love.Therefore I would recommend The Last Tinker to any gamer looking for a relaxed experience."
