76561198042371291,Recommended,260160,19575979,"Posted: 8 December, 2015",all,MrSharku,"I do recommend the game highly. I have played it for two hours total, and that's all the game might get out of me.That sounds hypocritical to you? Let me explain.The games environment is wonderful, the combat is simple yet fun. The characters are also fun and I just had a smile on my face for the most part. The game mechanics are fun and has a bit of relaxation to them yet it gives you a bit of adrenaline from time to time. I enjoyed the story thus far too.The problem is, if you have any controller other than the 360 controller, you're going to have a bad time starting this fun game. The first time is fine, second time maybe too. But after that, you won't be able to load your game. They have a major bug with other controllers (Xbox One for me) that forces you to scroll through the menu to the left constantly. Also any other settings you'd want to change with the controller are impossible. I set my controls in the beginning to controller only and even if I pull out my Xbox One controller, to try and navigate, I won't have much luck. Some button placement is also not properly linked with any controller other than the 360.So if you have a 360 controller, you'll love this game. If you have any other controller, it's better to skip the buy and wait for the company to fix it. I will just hope they'll fix it. Because it might be a game I'd want my future kids to play, but there won't be any 360 controllers around anymore by then, so they game would literally die out at one point."
