,Recommended,260160,29032523,Posted: 5 January,all,Anita,"The last tinker is a rather short game, but packed with tons of charm. It is clear throughout the whole game how the previous era of platformer games has influenced this game in its design. While it at times really did remind me of games like Spyro and Ratched & Clank, it still managed to keep an own sense of style and expression. Despite me having a bad first impression during the first hour of gameplay, the game managed to charm me over and I really enjoyed playing the rest of the game.ProsAbsolutely charming game with charming characters and charming environments.Love how the game used the contrast between chaos (sensory overload) and calm to help pace the game and setting the mood.Love the way the story as well as the visual story was developed and told during the later parts of the game.I liked the level progression. I didn’t feel like I was backtracking and the levels, although rather confined, always allowed for some extra exploration.ConsBad first impression. You, as the player, was dropped into a confusing place of sensory overload, utter chaos and fetch quests.The lag! I had some serious frame rate drops and had to toggle the graphics settings and turn some stuff off to even have the game in a playable state.Clunky camera and controls which lead to some frustrating situations.Initial combat felt clunky and unresponsive.Game was not consistent in telling the rules. Sometimes when you die, all defeated enemies will respawn and sometimes not."
