,Recommended,260160,19531409,"Posted: 6 December, 2015",all,Crabapple,"Review:The Last Tinker: City of Colors has got to be one of the best indie games I have ever played. It isn't the most difficult of games and not necassarily the best of the indie franchise, but it certainly has had some work put into it and it deserves to be recognized. And with that, let's get into this review.So to kick things off, let's talk about the story. The main character that you play as in The Last Tinker is Koru, who suprisingly enough, is the Last Tinker. Weird right? The place that this all takes place in is Colortown, where three factions of people live together; blue, red, and green. A race is held anually in Colortown and Koru always competes. But the night after the race, things go terribly wrong. A purple color element turns the world into bleak or in other words, white and gray. Now Koru most bring together the factions and their elements to stop the bleak from destroying Colortown. Although I may have left a few things out, I personally though that this story was although very simply and relatively childish, it was still fun and I thought it added to the game very well. Not much else to say about the story. Next, the gameplay.Ahhh, 3D platformers. Oh how you made my childhood amazing. This game is very reminiscent to me of Spyro: Dragonfly Dojo and Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. The gameplay is sort of an action 3D platformer. You also get new abilities for each element you collect and for each move you buy from the fighting expert. The combat was pretty unique too because once you got further into the game, you were given many options on how to take on your enemies with the power of the elements granted to you. There are also puzzles which you know aren't the most challenging thing, but you know... they're there :P. Now one thing I am sure people will want to know about this game is what are the controls like and should I have a controller? Gladly, the keyboard controls are good and a controller is not necassary. If you are a pleb like me, you don't have a controller for PC games. Althought the controls felt a little bit contradictory near the start of the game, you eventually get a good feel for them. Onto the look of the game!Honestly, this would probably be the main reason I like this game so much. The visuals are absolutely amazing in terms of variety and color. And that is what made me want to play it that much more, so I can restore color to Colortown so I can see the color again :D. Now of coures the game isn't exactly on my top list of best graphics, but man these visuals just draw you in that much more.The last thing I would like to issue is how the game is $20 at original price which brings up the question, is it worth $20? Well my personal answer to that question is no, no it is not. Although all of the things I said were good for the most part, this game is not worth $20. My first reason for it not being worth that much is because the game doesn't really have enough playthrough time and if you'd ask me, the game doesn't have much replayability. I consider my self a relatively average platform player and my playthrough was only like 5 to 6 hours. With $20, you could go buy something you can pour many hours into like *cough *cough Rocket League *cough *cough. I got the game on sale, so I would say I got worth out of it. Honestly, my best calculation of worth for gameplay is $2 = 1 hour. The second reason I would say this game is not worth $20 is because of the fact that there is much more time and value you can get out of 20 dollars. Unfortunately, this $20 price tag for a game that was released a little over a year ago for an indie game with a small amount of play time just makes the game not quite worth it. If you can get it on sale, definitely consider getting it because it is most certainly worth it if you can get it like that.Overall, my experience with this game was fantastic and worth the amount of money I put into it. If you can get this game on sale it is most definitely worth your money and I reccommend it. Please don't actually pay $20 for this game though if you have value in mind.Overview:Pros:1. Colorful2. Fun Gameplay3. A Simple, Yet Charming StoryCons:1. Not Worth $202. Lack of ReplabilityFinal Score | 8.5/10"
